\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b1\i0	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 I have already seen char as enviro in many different places (even if not always called that)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Perhaps not surprising given systems-focussed, cybernetic nature of computation and }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0 comp-art}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Sometimes explicit, sometimes not. Egs in the previous section show how it is coming hand-in-hand with the spatial turn, part of this historical movement.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b1\i0	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 AI architectures. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 AI architectures frequently about interaction of different parts (colony architecture, distributed AI (mostly this), \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91multi-agent systems\u8217\'92 (not all make a character or clear \u8216\'91entity\u8217\'92), object-oriented programming, SOAR, subsumption architecture, all the way up to BOD). Characters made up of nodes (but not characterised). Often away from real mind models to create functional, practical architectures. I used BOD b/c it was a simple implementation of these ideas, but also informed what I made - made char-as-enviro easier to make. But meant to be experienced in gestalt, not all the little bits. The architecture is supposed, often, to support a singular experience. Cheng\u8217\'92s BOB. Noel Welsh on animism in object-oriented programming. Explains its popularity/perserverence. \u8220\'93nimism provides a theory about why OOP is powerful: its particular style of modularization divides up a program so that animate thinking can be readily applied to any of its parts. Functional programming, on the other hand, provides a model that systematically excludes animism, which might explain why, despite its undeniable theoretical advantages, it has little popularity outside of a small research community."\u8221\'94 Galloway talking about the connections between \u8216\'91the structure of ontological systems [about the world] and the structure of the\u8230\'85 technologies of post-Fordist capitalism?\u8217\'92 }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b1\i0	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 In art, lots of environments that are wilful/meant to be interacted with in an animist sense.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 La Maison Sensible}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 Penny\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92s UZUME. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 One of Champion\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s as an example of this. Perhaps, in metaphor, }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 Dear Esther}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b1\i0	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Boss characters in videogames. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Particularly large and impressive enemies that take up for more of the player's narrative, spatial and strategic attention than other enemies \endash  in some cases, as in Shadow Of The Collosus, becoming 'living levels' in their own right. Sevastopol and the alien as one. Both environments to negotiate themselves (particularly God of War), and interpenetrated with existing environments.Gamasutra and Gameindustry.biz draw attention to them as a \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91test\u8217\'92 of what the player has learned - mostly this is environmental manipulation. In bounded arenas.\u8221\'94Even the shape of the environment bosses lurk in can be a crucial part of their design. \u8220\'93 A videogame boss is both a }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0 test}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  and a }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0 story}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Not a huge amount written on them (using undergrad thesis - focusses on their role as environments). Large size is important. Their \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91lair\u8217\'92 - tied to a particular place that is }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 part}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  of them. Examples of the player being followed through the game by bosses - sinistar, Prince of Persia: double troubl, Portal. The role of the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91epic\u8217\'92 , the \u8216\'91arena\u8217\'92. The biggest focus on a character in mechanical encounter. An intimacy. Bosses "can define a world, give it character and allow players to have a focal point when discussing moments within the game," says Kynan Pearson, creative director at Bluepoint Games. The mothership in phoenix. Killer Croc. Newman: \u8216\'91bosses usually require a more complex strategy\u8217\'92 - the boss is a puzzle, to newman. \u8220\'93Self-contained space\u8221\'94 - \u8220\'93character or mechanism\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b1\i0	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Examples in the previous section of an \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8216\'91econarratological perspective\u8217\'92, that looks at divides of personhood and environment.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  E.g. Everything - Alan Watts philosophy - An experiment in personhood - in what a character should be. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Tremendous connectedness of everything\u8221\'94 About the systematics of life and existence. Cheng creating interlapping characterised systems. Examples from the previous section. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b1\i0	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 My }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0 autocosmic}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0  methodology of \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8216\'91character-as-environment\u8217\'92 took a slightly different approach. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 About interacting with a character like it is an environment (unlike most AI architectures). Not a strict econarratological approach, away from the human/anthropomorphised character, like Cheng/Caracciolo approach. Not about a character interpenetrated with environment, like boss characters, or an environment that bears the memories/imprints of a character/the characters that lived within it. Characterisation not necessarily \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91spread out\u8217\'92 across the environment - just \u8216\'91normal\u8217\'92 comp. characters in another shape.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b1\i0	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Re-iterate the point of a autocosmic approach to this, and then proceed. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 It is about building something that is meant to be reacted to in some of the interpersonal, systemic ways that we relate to environments (egs from a variety of places, interdisciplinary).}
